  "tips": [
    "Although there are several trails that go up from Benasque to Cerler, this is perhaps one of the most traditional and important. It has several points along it from which to observe the views.",
    "The highest town in the Aragonese Pyrenees, with the Aramón Cerler alpine ski resort as the main sports engine for decades, it is also a good starting point for numerous trail running training routes.",
    "A good point from which to observe Benasque with the Tuca del Mont behind, as well as the planned expansions of the municipality.",
    "One of the most common viewpoints from which to observe Benasque due to its relative proximity to the town center, although it is still a fairly steep path.",
    "In addition to a beautiful town center, here you will find all kinds of tourist services, from shops to hotels and restaurants."
  ],
